Dialogue: 10,0:01:25.58,0:01:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's go for it.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:26.90,0:01:27.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, good.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:27.95,0:01:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me just a moment.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.92,0:01:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:37.08,0:01:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Calling already?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:39.08,0:01:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Early calling breeds self-destruction.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:42.13,0:01:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:42.77,0:01:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, didn't we warn you earlier?
Dialogue: 10,0:01:44.87,0:01:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Early calling breeds self-destruction.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:49.67,0:01:51.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This ain't gonna go well for you, buddy.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:51.86,0:01:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It changes the flow of tiles too much.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:55.41,0:01:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:09.83,0:02:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:14.50,0:02:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Toitoi Kan-tsumo{informal term for Rinshan Kaihou (valued at 1 han)} Dora 3. {all pungs; winning hand consisting of four pungs or kongs and one pair​}{please never do that again, it's disgusting}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.49,0:02:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a haneman. {win worth 12000 points (or, if dealer, 18000 points)}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.50,0:02:21.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsk... I'm all out of luck. \NI'll have to pay it myself.{I shouldn't take it for granted next time.} {guess} {2nd part is "ore no hitori-barai da", which is referring to the rule of "sekinin-barai", which means you're responsible for paying the full value of the hand, even when it was tsumo, alone, because you're the one who gave the tile used in the kan, which enabled them to win the hand}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:21.99,0:02:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And this north was the fourth tile. All right! {there's only 4 of each tile in the game, so he's saying indirectly that Ryuu got the last available one}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:27.78,0:02:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,By the way, aren't you that mysterious mahjong rogue they talk about lately? {nc what's jangoro, seems to be some specific name they use to refer to ryuu, I suspect jan part comes from mahJANg and goro is "racketeer; thug; rogue; bully; fixer"}{Yup, the idea of Jangoro got translated a Rep Player in Akagi and Mahjong wanderer in Shin Janki, if I recall correctly}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.50,0:02:35.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Always with a cigarette in your right hand and a nervous look.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:36.29,0:02:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:39.28,0:02:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, a toitoi chanta? {nc}{Tancha = Toitoi+chanta}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:40.76,0:02:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Discarding the 2-sou after a 1-sou pon, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.82,0:02:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's nasty.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.29,0:02:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, either way you can only have Honitsu, or perhaps Chanta?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:48.02,0:02:50.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,Now, what should I cut{or "discard"} here?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.57,0:02:53.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,Discarding the 2-sou after the 1-sou pon means
Dialogue: 10,0:02:53.54,0:02:57.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,he could've had a wait on a 3-sou, which means...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:57.37,0:03:00.03,Thought,,0,0,0,,The dora, 5-sou, is dangerous.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.03,0:03:01.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is a war of nerves.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.78,0:03:03.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,Just what is on his mind?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.41,0:03:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Make a move already.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:05.48,0:03:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The clock is ticking, \Nand it ain't just for you. {prefer the "Time's not yours to waste" ver}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.30,0:03:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You jerk!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:08.81,0:03:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop playing dumb!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.04,0:03:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What is it?! Can it be a ron? {idk how to work around the "masaka :o"}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.16,0:03:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.60,0:03:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Xia{yakuhai - 1 han} Chun{yakuhai - 1 han} Toitoi, mangan.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:23.83,0:03:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,A shanpon{wait pattern, having two pairs and waiting to fill one triplet} on middle tiles?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:26.54,0:03:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You fucker threw that 2-sou as a trap! {to trap me/to deceive me/to throw me off}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:32.17,0:03:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Manager, this ain't looking good. {chapter 9}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.34,0:03:39.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If we put that rogue up against those guys, they'll cause some trouble for sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:39.07,0:03:41.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just some punk who doesn't know his place.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:41.25,0:03:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,If he keeps playing like that, \Nhe'll get himself killed anyway.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:47.41,0:03:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's a pon!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.84,0:03:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey buddy, regret calling that already?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:51.15,0:03:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,If you were going for a 123 Sanshoku...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.93,0:03:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd want to call the 2-sou here.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.52,0:03:59.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:00.34,0:04:02.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There, I finally caught up.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:02.20,0:04:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Buddy, flip the kan-dora, will ya?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.56,0:04:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa, that's not bad either! {or "That's another kan!"}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:12.95,0:04:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You only get that by kanning{can I really do that for "kan"? most likely not, but "doing kan" is awkward}! Luck's on my side now.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.05,0:04:21.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,Honitsu Toitoi Chun Dora 4, baiman. Alright, let's end this in one shot!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.09,0:04:23.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not in this for much longer. {lit: your back is sooty - I don't understand the metaphor, but essentially it's ryuu's way of saying "you're already dead" - in manga he's sort of like grim reaper as anyone he says this to dies soon; https://manba.co.jp/topics/21894}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:25.83,0:04:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.09,0:04:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, bud, you said I'm not in this for longer - what did you mean by that?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.64,0:04:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better explain yourself, lest we arrive to some painful misunderstanding.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.85,0:04:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd ya like it? I have San-kantsu on top of it now! {with san-kantsu, he added 2 more han to his hand, making it go to up Sanbaiman}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.11,0:04:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Ron.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.15,0:04:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Ron?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:54.02,0:04:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't ya just pon the 3-sou now?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.62,0:05:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Asshole! Think you can get away with making fun of me?!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.06,0:05:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.37,0:05:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Ishikawa Takashi, the second boss of the Kai Group,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.24,0:05:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,here to represent the interests of my predecessor Kai Shozo. {no clue what's shoumei}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.61,0:05:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you are the Dragon. {his real name is not ryuu}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:23.69,0:05:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Did you say Dragon? \N{\i1}The{\i0} Calling Dragon? {popular translation of this title is "crying dragon" but I think it's a mistranslation because "naki" is used more often as "to cry" but in this case it's "to call [a combination in mahjong]", like when they shout "Ron/Tsumo" during games}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:27.42,0:05:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, our boss risked his life investigating you, just to see you
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.99,0:06:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it, you dipshit!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.26,0:06:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you hear me telling you to stop?!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:07.10,0:06:09.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Let him go.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:12.29,0:07:16.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On that day, Kai Shouzou lived within Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:37.77,0:07:40.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Kai Shozo raised Ishikawa Takashi and always looked after him,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:40.79,0:07:44.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,because he believed Ishikawa to be capable of carrying on his back the future
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.76,0:07:47.73,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of the Kai Group and the entire Oudou Syndicate.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.75,0:07:52.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa arrived at a certain general hospital in Tokyo.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.20,0:07:54.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He was there to check on Sakurada Michizo,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.17,0:07:56.57,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the head of the Oudou Syndicate, who was shot at
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.57,0:08:00.78,Narrator,,0,0,0,,by a member of Miyoshi Group because of their prolonged feud with the Kai Group. {I hope your brain is melting already, mine sure does}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:00.78,0:08:05.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,For Ishikawa, that meant that everyone's expectations of him were set high.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.65,0:08:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You guys will wait here.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:09.22,0:08:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,"High expectations." {omoki omowaku - lit: "heavy heaviments" (expectations) - was used in previous line as well, it seems they're very fond of this phrase for some reason}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.05,0:08:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Namely, the dying wish of the head of the Kai Group,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:13.79,0:08:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,former lieutenant of the Oudou Syndicate, Kai Shozo,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:16.89,0:08:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that would become his final assignment for Ishikawa.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.06,0:08:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job, boys.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.50,0:08:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to ask, but could you kick that door open for me? {no idea what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.03,0:08:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,With all due respect, sir, \Nthis place is run by the Kawachi Group.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.80,0:08:31.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No one is allowed to enter without the boss' permission.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.21,0:08:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Interesting, I didn't know that.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:35.08,0:08:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I am Ishikawa, the second boss of the Kai Group,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.83,0:08:40.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet he still won't open for me?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:42.64,0:08:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Coward! Open this door at once! {no clue what's this sanpin}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:51.89,0:08:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if it isn't boss Kawachi? \NLong time no see.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:00.44,0:09:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa, what did you come here for?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.00,0:09:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been put in charge of boss' hospital room. It's none of your business. {I have no idea what is going on anymore so from now on I'm just gonna leave the most literal, uninspired translations - it doesn't make sense, but at least it's not wrong; I'm sure nobody among the japanese audience could tell what's going on now either so fuck it - it's not our fault the show is a mess that's impossible to follow}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:08.68,0:09:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I came to check on the boss.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.45,0:09:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.48,0:09:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you seriously telling me that you didn't know that only those
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.39,0:09:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,who shared a cup of sake with the old man can get to meet him? {oyaji is "father" but that makes absolutely no sense}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:21.92,0:09:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason I came here today is to share a cup with the boss.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:26.16,0:09:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:28.43,0:09:32.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa, who do you think you are \Nto be allowed to drink sake with him?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:32.86,0:09:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind you, it was the fight your predecessor, Kai started,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.57,0:09:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,that brought our old man to this state.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.71,0:09:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa, you asshole!
Dialogue: 10,0:09:44.43,0:09:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:51.05,0:09:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not moving an inch from here until I get to share a cup with him!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:01.16,0:10:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Oudou and Kai are the two strongest organizations in Eastern Japan,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.93,0:10:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,with undisputed mastery over the Kanto region.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.20,0:10:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That makes the Kai Group, with 2,000 men in its ranks,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:11.14,0:10:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the most important group in my organization. {no clue what's chokkei, assumed this is kai shozo}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:13.51,0:10:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't tolerate anyone messing with their "night" businesses.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:16.64,0:10:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hit them, they hit back two or three times harder. {chapter 4 of manga}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:21.18,0:10:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the Yakuza for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.18,0:10:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not interested in listening to your boasting.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.36,0:10:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going home.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:27.68,0:10:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:31.25,0:10:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Dragon. You know I'll make you mine.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:34.73,0:10:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I am quite certain that you have it in you - \Nthe thing I'm looking for.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:38.40,0:10:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're absolutely fearless, \Nthat's an important gift.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.04,0:10:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But not as much as your extraordinary luck.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:47.30,0:10:50.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it ever since we first met at the boss's mansion -
Dialogue: 10,0:10:50.74,0:10:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,you're a monster, who lives by fighting alone.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:55.32,0:10:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So? Why don't you become mine and keep growing as a player?
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.72,0:11:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, the boss also has a lot of admiration for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.55,0:11:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I answer to nobody. I'm not anyone's property.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.81,0:11:09.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, I carry on my back the lives of 2,000 members of the Kai Group.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.33,0:11:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What of it?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:11.40,0:11:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, you shouldn't humiliate me like that with your rudeness.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.20,0:11:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to set an example for everyone!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:46.50,0:11:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.19,0:11:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You're hoarding souzu tiles this time, huh.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.70,0:11:52.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, buddy, don't get carried away.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:52.11,0:11:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You may have been winning so far, \Nbut it was through sheer luck.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:56.20,0:12:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Mahjong is a game you can only win if you have the skill.  {lol, lmao}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.72,0:12:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch closely, buddy. I'm about to show you what real mahjong is.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.72,0:12:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There it goes! {?}{I have no idea either}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:06.19,0:12:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that only one thing matters in mahjong.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:10.23,0:12:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the victory.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.46,0:12:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:17.53,0:12:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-You! It wasn't souzu?!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.32,0:12:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:41.31,0:12:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What was that?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.49,0:12:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Gunshots?! {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:44.81,0:12:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.13,0:12:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon... Dragon, you...
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.79,0:12:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon! Give me your luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:59.02,0:13:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it to the old man, Dragon! {no clue if that's how he refers to himself}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.45,0:13:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa may enter.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:18.49,0:13:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?{no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:19.43,0:13:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The boss is going to meet him.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:26.43,0:13:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Shozo... {chapter 11}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:28.34,0:13:32.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,Please, ma'am, \Ntake good care of Ishikawa.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.44,0:13:35.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,With time, he'll be the only man strong enough
Dialogue: 10,0:13:35.21,0:13:37.78,Thought,,0,0,0,,to carry the fate of Oudou and Kai on his back.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.78,0:13:40.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,The only thing that can defeat him is luck.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:40.42,0:13:45.22,Thought,,0,0,0,,If he had luck, he could be the man to rule over all of Japan!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.75,0:13:51.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Sakurada Michizo's last child, Ishikawa Takashi, is now born.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:57.12,0:13:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:58.97,0:14:02.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,You continuously kept refusing even my predecessor, the first boss,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:02.04,0:14:05.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,but I, Ishikawa, will definitely make you play for me.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.67,0:14:10.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,With your luck, I can become the best in Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:13.11,0:14:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, bud, how are you planning to get out of this?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.09,0:14:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:22.92,0:14:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The one crying will be you. {muzu help}{just ignore it or put a TL note explaining that 泣く and 哭く are pronounced the same}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:34.89,0:14:38.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,Dragon. Dragon!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:38.07,0:14:42.44,Thought,,0,0,0,,I just wished to spend one more joyous evening playing mahjong with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:07.92,0:15:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,B-Bastard! You'll regret making fun of the Yakuza!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.43,0:15:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll kill you! {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:14.66,0:15:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, come with us for a moment.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:17.66,0:15:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss Ishikawa is determined to play against you.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:21.05,0:15:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Dragon? The Calling Dragon?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.44,0:15:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you refuse...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.58,0:15:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll die.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:32.19,0:15:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell this to your Ishikawa: my life...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.98,0:15:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My very cheap life, is heavily overestimated.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:40.96,0:15:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Ishikawa's goons! {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.21,0:15:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't you taking the tough image too far?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:45.97,0:15:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess the whole group starts acting up when the boss changes, eh?! {chapter 12}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:50.11,0:15:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have you know that the guy you've got a gun on is one of my men!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.99,0:16:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it, Dragon. \NWho said you can leave?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.98,0:16:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, it must be fate that we meet again here.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:06.39,0:16:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a long while \Nsince you last played me.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.99,0:16:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Murota took Dragon?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.76,0:16:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:14.00,0:16:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Murota said if you want Dragon, you must take him by force.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:17.76,0:16:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh... I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:20.71,0:16:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So Murota took Dragon...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.95,0:16:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy is using Dragon to try me. \NTry me, Ishikawa Takashi!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.46,0:16:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,How should I deal with him?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.45,0:16:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,How would a man, entrusted with the lives of 2,000 men by the first boss, act?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.45,0:16:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It took me ten years to be able to speak in front of the president.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.66,0:16:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you understand, dragon?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:46.00,0:16:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You said you hate the Yakuza right off the bat.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:49.87,0:16:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to the Umemiya Gambling House where we first met.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:54.04,0:16:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm still amazed by your method of playing even now when I remember it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:58.65,0:17:02.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Just doing one pon after the other and gettin' a Tsuuisou{yakuman} like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.46,0:17:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:06.98,0:17:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that woman I rewarded you with doing well?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:14.10,0:17:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was also the one who introduced you to the boss after that.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.58,0:17:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Imbecile! When you meet the boss, \Nyou greet him with a bow! {no clue what's izatsuite}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:31.55,0:17:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The memory of his encounter with Kaito was brought back to life in Dragon's mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:46.28,0:17:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your turn.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.78,0:17:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.65,0:17:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.\NPinfu Ittsuu. Right. {third chapter of manga}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:16.09,0:18:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.\NTanyao Iipeiko.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:18.93,0:18:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,2,000 all.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.10,0:18:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you a Yakuza?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.49,0:18:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm? What'd you just say, kid?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.63,0:18:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't it considered shameful for a Yakuza to deceive others?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:30.27,0:18:32.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Why don't you take those sunglasses off?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:33.14,0:18:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like the fun and games are over, Shozo.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.04,0:18:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems I'm losing my knack, boss.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:38.56,0:18:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,To think I'd be caught by a kid of all people...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.72,0:18:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Not bad, kid.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:43.77,0:18:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like Murota didn't even notice.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:53.26,0:18:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Boss Kai is calling you!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:56.10,0:18:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.47,0:19:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If he needs something, \Nhe can come with his own feet.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.84,0:19:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You prick!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.21,0:19:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you can't lay a finger on that guy!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.84,0:19:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That guy is mine, \Nlet him do as he pleases.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.85,0:19:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.04,0:19:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, it's better that you don't take the Yakuza lightly. {chapter 12}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.42,0:19:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be quite well-off with us.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:21.59,0:19:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.92,0:19:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:26.19,0:19:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Professional gamblers deceive people for a living. {no clue what's bagujujihan}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.96,0:19:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, aren't they the perfect prey for you? {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.57,0:19:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:34.87,0:19:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I hit the bull's-eye, didn't I?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:36.73,0:19:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You even gave up on a San-ankou to make me draw that.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:40.70,0:19:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You've done well, for some feeble 1,000 points.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.11,0:19:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Come clean, you. {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.71,0:19:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Don't mess with me! {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.36,0:19:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.02,0:19:59.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Goin' for a Ryuuiisou now?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.16,0:20:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, it seems to me you never lose.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:02.49,0:20:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But those who don't know the pain of losing, don't know what a true battle is.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:07.20,0:20:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,He who gets up first after a defeat is the strongest.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.27,0:20:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:15.16,0:20:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, I'm going to let you taste the anguish of defeat now.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:20.51,0:20:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not in this for much longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.14,0:20:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What? What do you mean I'm not in this for longer?!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.45,0:20:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:28.69,0:20:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.25,0:20:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,You're calling the tile you just discarded you bastard?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.43,0:20:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Asshole, it ain't a Ryuuiisou? {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:35.30,0:20:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't carry the burden of even a single person on your back. {chapter 8}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:39.79,0:20:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Unwavering faith in yourself is required to win.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.54,0:20:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If the taste of defeat still lingers in your mouth, you've already lost. {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:02.89,0:21:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Kawachi sent his small fry for us. {I'm gonna stop saying guess now, there are more lines that are one than there are ones where I'm certain what they're saying}{still chapter 12}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.73,0:21:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If you know that I'm the second boss of the Kai Group,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:09.26,0:21:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa Takashi, don't hesitate
Dialogue: 10,0:21:10.77,0:21:11.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and shoot!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.44,0:21:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't hit me, huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.90,0:21:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This bulletproof glass is the proof the Kai Clan has nothing to fear from you! {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.18,0:21:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The conference was a mess, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:24.30,0:21:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Even before the boss' memorial service was over, a huge internal feud broke out. {chapter 13}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.85,0:21:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The rumor is some men from the Kawachi Group
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.66,0:21:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,already went missing without a trace.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.82,0:21:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it the Kai Group who did it?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.75,0:21:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Some say, the Kawachi Group fabricated it themselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:36.83,0:21:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But that guy Ishikawa Takashi, the current leader of the Kai Group,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:40.40,0:21:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,has great acumen, isn't that what they say?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:44.80,0:21:46.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Dragon knew it full well -
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.53,0:21:51.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,it won't be long before Ishikawa Takashi would stand in his way.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:51.91,0:21:57.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was his intuition of a man who had lived his whole live amidst conflict.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:58.25,0:22:01.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Dragon's blood was boiling.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:07.56,0:22:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:13.06,0:22:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Got no time for a kan, eh. {basically they're saying he's calling too early and didn't wait enough to have a triplet to call kan from}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:17.66,0:22:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a ron.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:19.87,0:22:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Chinitsu Toitoi Tanyao!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:23.90,0:22:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I've heard the rumors, but it seems even they don't do you justice.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:27.34,0:22:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you Miyoshi-san?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:29.84,0:22:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So you knew who I was from the start?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:33.65,0:22:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not my first game with a Yakuza.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:35.57,0:22:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What was that?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:46.36,0:22:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,F-Fuckers...
Dialogue: 10,0:22:51.40,0:22:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,K-Kai…
Dialogue: 10,0:22:54.54,0:22:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{Huh?}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:56.57,0:23:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Long time no see, Dragon. You're just one tile away from Suukantsu, eh? {muzu help}{it's right}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:00.51,0:23:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking for you, \Nbut I also got to meet Miyoshi, it seems.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:03.60,0:23:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I should be grateful to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:05.58,0:23:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Spare me your thanks.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:06.65,0:23:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Just calling off your dogs that follow my every step would be enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:12.55,0:23:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You're as unamiable as ever. {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:15.12,0:23:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Motherfucker...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:21.53,0:23:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:22.92,0:23:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Miyoshi, it's your turn. \NWhat's taking you so long? {no clue; chapter 5}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:32.51,0:23:33.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.46,0:23:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:41.08,0:23:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm waiting, Dragon. \NYou and me still have a game to play.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:45.82,0:23:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, you always play with your life on the line.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.29,0:23:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,For that reason, I'll put my life on the line as well.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.73,0:23:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be our first and last life-or-death battle!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.73,0:24:05.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The battle that night was impressed vividly into Dragon's mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:05.14,0:24:08.14,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was at the metropolitan office of the Oudou Syndicate
Dialogue: 10,0:24:08.14,0:24:10.61,Narrator,,0,0,0,,where Boss Sakurada invited his close associate,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:10.61,0:24:13.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Maruko Sadagoro, for a game with Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:14.05,0:24:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:16.92,0:24:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:19.34,0:24:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, if I win, you'll be mine.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:23.79,0:24:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you win, you're free to do whatever you want with my life.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:27.83,0:24:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:31.98,0:24:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:33.60,0:24:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Kai has been calling in retaliation to Dragon. {muzu help, I see meaning of haru "to become one tile away from completion"; chapter 7 for ref} {Kai's calling everytime Ryuu calls, to "get on pace" with him, as if he's pursuing Ryuu by calling the same amount as him}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:37.33,0:24:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Audentes fortuna iuvat. {more muzu, "nothing ventured, nothing gained"}{it's just 虎穴に入らずんば虎子を得ず}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:40.18,0:24:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,This was the tactic that Maruko taught Kai.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:44.78,0:24:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Chun Honitsu!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:50.14,0:24:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That night, it was as though Kai pulled tiles at will.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:53.76,0:24:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He had the heavens on his side.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:57.16,0:24:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,At last, "All Last." {オーラス "All Last" is how some players refer to the last round of the game}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:02.83,0:25:07.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,Dragon discarded the 5-pin and I can see all 4 of them.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:07.53,0:25:10.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,The 7-pin is safe. {dumbass, that's not how kabe works}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:12.80,0:25:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:18.02,0:25:19.24,Thought,,0,0,0,,A closed 7-pin{ wait}!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:22.12,0:25:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, was that Chi necessary?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:24.42,0:25:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't win with a haneman tsumo or a sanbaiman from one of us...
Dialogue: 10,0:25:27.56,0:25:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,you got no chance to win. {this game}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:29.51,0:25:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not stealing tiles with my calls.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:32.13,0:25:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm imbuing them with life.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:35.86,0:25:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop meddling in my affairs.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:39.10,0:25:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Another 7-pin, what a hassle. {he's just commenting on how persistent the 7-pin is, given how he drew another one right after discarding it}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:43.83,0:25:46.81,Thought,,0,0,0,,What on earth is Dragon waiting on?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:46.81,0:25:49.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,Could it be another 7-pin?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:49.48,0:25:51.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,It can't be pinzu again... {clueless, this guy is}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:51.48,0:25:53.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine, I'm in luck today!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:53.51,0:25:55.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,The heavens are on my side.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:57.55,0:25:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Shozo!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:58.42,0:26:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Shozo, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:00.09,0:26:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I-It's nothing.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:02.69,0:26:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Sit the fuck down and relax.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:06.28,0:26:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon! Let's settle this!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:13.57,0:26:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:18.70,0:26:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Dragon...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:20.61,0:26:22.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Dragon...
Dialogue: 10,0:26:21.34,0:26:23.03,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Shozo, think about yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:28.50,0:26:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,What a wonderful victory!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:31.09,0:26:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold up, Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:33.70,0:26:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't forgotten about the settlement, have you?! {from manga, no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:38.36,0:26:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,A promise is a promise! \NYou must take my life now!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:48.60,0:26:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute, Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:51.96,0:26:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have a hint of humanity in you,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:53.67,0:26:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you leave without even acknowledging Kai's words?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.54,0:27:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter... Kai's wife, \Nshe didn't tell anyone else, but...
Dialogue: 10,0:27:01.48,0:27:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A 12 mm bullet has lodged in his lung.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:05.29,0:27:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It needs to be taken out as soon as possible!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:08.94,0:27:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,However, he only has a fifty-fifty chance of surviving the operation...
Dialogue: 10,0:27:12.53,0:27:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He absolutely refused to undergo the surgery!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:15.80,0:27:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter held onto me as she cried....
Dialogue: 10,0:27:19.77,0:27:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,He only has three months left...\NAnd Kai bet those three months
Dialogue: 10,0:27:24.71,0:27:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,on you!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:26.50,0:27:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say another word, old man...
Dialogue: 10,0:27:29.46,0:27:32.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're making me look pathetic.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:32.03,0:27:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Dragon?\NHurry up and take my life!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:36.25,0:27:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:39.62,0:27:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't you say that you're carrying the burden of 2,000 people on your back?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:44.36,0:27:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Cherish that burden.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:47.49,0:27:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon...
Dialogue: 10,0:28:08.32,0:28:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,B-Boss!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:11.25,0:28:13.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What? The boss was shot?!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:13.25,0:28:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,They sent an armed assassin?! {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:14.72,0:28:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Kai was right there with him - \Nwhat's the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:20.29,0:28:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg you humbly.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:22.20,0:28:24.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let the boss perish now. {assuming sakurada is still alive and in the hospital, also don't understand a word of this highbrow yakuza dialect}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:24.53,0:28:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,All I've done up to this point
Dialogue: 10,0:28:27.07,0:28:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,was to expedite his ascent to the position of the strongest boss in all of Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:30.76,0:28:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You may claim my own life several times over!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:34.04,0:28:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't let the boss perish now!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:37.81,0:28:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm begging you humbly...
Dialogue: 10,0:29:10.24,0:29:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt you might come home today.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:13.05,0:29:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been waiting here for quite a while.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:38.57,0:29:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,"Auspicious Alliance", huh? \NQuite the witty name they've picked. {Koichi Kawachi's name is 幸一 (the guy in the middle), Koyu is 幸友 - "ko-friends" - took translation from manga, otherwise considered "koyu group" (chapter 14 btw)}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:44.07,0:29:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what happens, that stinking scum doesn't seem to know what shame is.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:49.65,0:29:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Men that have no shame don't deserve to live.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:54.29,0:29:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Tamura?
Dialogue: 10,0:29:56.62,0:29:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss... Today's the day.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:58.58,0:30:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so? Finally the day of his weekly visit to his mistress?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:03.10,0:30:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We have people on standby at her apartment complex. {going by logic, no idea what he actually says}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:05.55,0:30:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Tamura, get out of the country by tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:09.04,0:30:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can kick back and relax in Manila. Sounds good, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:30:13.06,0:30:17.10,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, a seed of uneasiness\Nsprouted in Ishikawa's mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:17.10,0:30:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:18.75,0:30:21.84,Narrator,,0,0,0,,He hoped to dispel that uneasiness with the ura dora...
Dialogue: 10,0:30:22.32,0:30:23.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 10,0:30:23.34,0:30:26.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,he couldn't find even a scrap of good luck. {from manga, nc what's tsuki} {tsuki is luck}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:40.53,0:30:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:41.67,0:30:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It must have been a lot of work.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:44.81,0:30:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,To think that the bait I've set would work this well... {no clue what's wara}
Dialogue: 10,0:30:48.72,0:30:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, Ishikawa also underestimates me.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:54.65,0:30:55.85,Default,,0,0,0,,In other news,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:56.42,0:31:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At Narita Bypass around 6 a.m. this morning, a car had burst into flames.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:00.85,0:31:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The passengers were all pronounced dead at the scene.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:03.26,0:31:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on his personal belongings, one of the victims
Dialogue: 10,0:31:05.43,0:31:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,was identified as Tamura Koichi,
Dialogue: 10,0:31:06.87,0:31:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Kai Group, part of the Oudou Syndicate.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:08.82,0:31:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, bullet marks were found on the bodies.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:11.85,0:31:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Some suggest that it was related to the shootout
Dialogue: 10,0:31:14.60,0:31:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that occurred at an apartment complex in Setagaya last night.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:17.84,0:31:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The authorities believe
Dialogue: 10,0:31:19.14,0:31:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that this is one of a growing number of internal conflicts within the Oudou Group.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:22.54,0:31:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,An emergency investigation
Dialogue: 10,0:31:24.04,0:31:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,into the "Auspicious Alliance", that split off from that organization, has started.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:28.88,0:31:30.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This was Ishikawa Takashi's first taste
Dialogue: 10,0:31:30.92,0:31:33.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,of humiliation, which shook his determination to the core.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:35.42,0:31:37.92,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It seemed like one man was looking at him
Dialogue: 10,0:31:37.92,0:31:42.52,Narrator,,0,0,0,,through a clearing in the dark clouds, sneering at him.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:42.52,0:31:46.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That man was not Kawachi, \Nand it was certainly not Murota....
Dialogue: 10,0:32:00.68,0:32:04.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,2,000 lives were weighing heavily on Ishikawa's back. {chapter 15}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:06.55,0:32:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's Dragon! Bring that goddamn Dragon to me!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:10.49,0:32:16.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa Takashi went for the only gamble that could support his plans.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:17.06,0:32:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, I got a tsumo!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:19.57,0:32:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Menhon{concealed Honitsu, is worth 1 han more than open honitsu, which is why it's specified by some players} ittsuu tsumo, double nan... {from manga}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:22.56,0:32:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,A baiman!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:29.94,0:32:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like you're out of luck today.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:32.68,0:32:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The point gap is almost 8,000 points now!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:35.55,0:32:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd ya like a little hanchan with a sashiuma{an extra payment between players, basically (for more info, there's https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/ウマ_(麻雀)#差しウマ)} between us?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:39.35,0:32:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the rate?
Dialogue: 10,0:32:40.30,0:32:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How does a hand sound? Plus time.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:43.75,0:32:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That is, if I win, you'll have to give me a hand, and come with me for a while... {from manga, no clue what he means}{ ͡° ͜ʖ ͡°}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:51.75,0:32:57.07,Thought,,0,0,0,,A kan on the 6-pin. If he's going for a sanshoku, then he's got a 6-sou triplet.
Dialogue: 10,0:32:57.07,0:33:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't mind your little sashiuma, I'll riichi!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:01.24,0:33:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:03.50,0:33:06.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,I knew it, he had that 6-sou triplet.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:07.11,0:33:09.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,He just let the 6-sou pass.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:09.18,0:33:12.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,If he's waiting on the 4th 9-sou, it can't be anythin' but Kokushi. {Kokushi Musou, a yakuman}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:13.05,0:33:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's play! {shoubu here is mostly used in a "do or die" way, a lot of mahjong players do that when throwing a risky tile}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:17.06,0:33:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanshoku Doukou{informally called Dou-pon because it's the sanshoku comprised of triplets/pon (I just saw it being called this way here and in Tetsuya)} Dora 2, mangan.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:20.12,0:33:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,T-Then, the 5-sou would've passed? {lit "the 5-sou wouldn't have have completed your hand?"}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:23.36,0:33:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That was your winning tile too, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:25.67,0:33:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Your boss has come up with quite the elaborate scheme.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:29.64,0:33:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here under direct orders from boss Ishikawa.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:34.13,0:33:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What? \NSo you just used me to test the waters? {lit: I was a stallion brought close to a mare to test her readiness to mate}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:37.63,0:33:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In any case, we haven't got much time. \NLet's conclude the next game at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:41.61,0:33:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If I win, Dragon will follow me to meet Ishikawa.
Dialogue: 10,0:33:52.75,0:33:55.16,Default,,0,0,0,,He discarded a pair of the chun?! {manga}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:55.16,0:33:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I didn't think you'd do something so foolish...
Dialogue: 10,0:33:58.47,0:34:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd better not be making fun of us!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:02.64,0:34:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:16.18,0:34:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The only one who believes is yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:18.55,0:34:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The only one who you can believe in is yourself.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:23.72,0:34:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing personal, but this game ends here.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:27.22,0:34:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, I'm the one who accepted boss Ishikawa's final orders.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:32.17,0:34:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,People call me a hitman...
Dialogue: 10,0:34:34.47,0:34:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just behave yourself and come with me to the boss's place.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:41.27,0:34:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So in the end, it seems the boss didn't have faith in either of us.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:45.21,0:34:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this round isn't over yet!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:58.73,0:35:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, excuse the repetition, but I'm going to say this once more.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:02.28,0:35:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss Ishikawa made me into what i am.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:05.65,0:35:09.06,Default,,0,0,0,,If he calls something black, then it's black, even if it's actually white.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:09.06,0:35:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,My life is entirely in boss Ishikawa's hands...
Dialogue: 10,0:35:13.16,0:35:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon...
Dialogue: 10,0:35:14.56,0:35:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't make me have to kill you.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:36.76,0:35:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What?! They've killed Takashina?
Dialogue: 10,0:35:39.93,0:35:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it! Bring everyone to the main office! {literally unintelligible without manga lol}
Dialogue: 10,0:35:43.83,0:35:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa, you punk!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:46.83,0:35:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:48.10,0:35:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Mangan.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:58.99,0:36:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon... You really are quite strange!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:03.02,0:36:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You discarded the same tiles as me in the last two rounds as well!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:07.20,0:36:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They're even in the same order. {from manga, pls check muzu}
Dialogue: 10,0:36:10.63,0:36:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon! Is it a coincidence, or is there some purpose to this matching game?!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:16.49,0:36:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Show me your hand!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:18.74,0:36:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The tiles one discards are the outer world.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:21.51,0:36:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The tiles in one's hand are the inner world.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:23.88,0:36:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,One's insides are the one thing that can't be shown.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:26.74,0:36:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, I want to see those "insides" of yours!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:37.69,0:36:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon...
Dialogue: 10,0:36:40.20,0:36:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you... Are you trying to mock me?!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:43.86,0:36:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 10,0:36:55.61,0:36:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Don't you know? {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:36:59.51,0:37:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What did you say?! \NThey got the chief?!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:03.35,0:37:07.12,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Underboss Murota Sakae was shot in the street.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:07.12,0:37:08.54,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Upon hearing that news,
Dialogue: 10,0:37:08.54,0:37:12.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the syndicate's adviser and a dozen members hurried to confirm it.{chapter 17}
Dialogue: 10,0:37:12.22,0:37:15.19,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Perhaps due to the inclement weather, the phone line was out of service.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:15.19,0:37:18.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In any case, they made a beeline straight for the designated hospital.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:18.80,0:37:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon,
Dialogue: 10,0:37:20.26,0:37:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,my draws are getting very interesting now that I'm playing against you!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:23.74,0:37:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps I'm grabbing hold of some of that monstrous luck of yours?
Dialogue: 10,0:37:28.21,0:37:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:32.28,0:37:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? \NWhy isn't everyone here yet?!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:34.80,0:37:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,W-Well... There was a call from the police saying that you had been shot...
Dialogue: 10,0:37:39.39,0:37:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You fools! \NI am clearly just fine!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:50.32,0:37:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Murota! It's the end of the road!
Dialogue: 10,0:37:59.33,0:38:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, there's no such thing as "impossible" for you.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:02.13,0:38:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I'm not one to believe in such fantasies! {manga, no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:38:05.01,0:38:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon! Let me introduce you to the concept of impossible!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:16.51,0:38:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Too bad, Dragon.\NJust a tanyao.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:32.27,0:38:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Ishikawa...
Dialogue: 10,0:38:35.60,0:38:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi ippatsu tsumo\Ntanyao and San-ankou, haneman! {muzu pls} {can't make out the word after "riichi", but the rest is ok and make up the points needed for a haneman}
Dialogue: 10,0:38:39.96,0:38:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:40.94,0:38:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see the two chrysanthemum flowers in between the doorframe?
Dialogue: 10,0:38:45.82,0:38:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The big one is for Murota, \Nand soon there will be one more!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:50.09,0:38:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Next to Murota's will be another flower - \Na deep crimson chrysanthemum!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:56.40,0:39:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately for you, Dragon, \NI won't let go of your luck until then!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:02.56,0:39:05.57,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're laughing at me, huh, Dragon?
Dialogue: 10,0:39:06.24,0:39:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't given in to your luck yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:09.58,0:39:13.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Furthermore... I'm not so foolish to rely on the luck of other people.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:21.98,0:39:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You've finally gained enough momentum to start mocking me, Dragon!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:25.03,0:39:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Good! I'll take you on this round!
Dialogue: 10,0:39:32.50,0:39:35.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is Dragon's tile, I can't discard it. {muzu pls; こいつあるようなあたりだけちゃうならねぇ} {he's just saying he can't discard the tile because Ryuu might use it}
Dialogue: 10,0:39:43.10,0:39:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, Dragon, it's a 2-pin. {muzu}
Dialogue: 10,0:39:48.87,0:39:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:50.35,0:39:54.42,Thought,,0,0,0,,That sly Dragon... \NWhat on earth is he waiting for?
Dialogue: 10,0:39:58.58,0:40:01.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,Impossible? No... Possible!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:03.06,0:40:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I win!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:13.26,0:40:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I see now, Dragon. Are you doing that just to spite me at any cost? {no clue}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:22.72,0:40:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:23.82,0:40:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You truly are The Calling Dragon
Dialogue: 10,0:40:28.11,0:40:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:32.78,0:40:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you release a flash of light with every call.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:39.52,0:40:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:42.07,0:40:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yet another flash.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:44.47,0:40:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,But no matter how hard you try, I will emerge victorious in the end!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:48.73,0:40:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon! Just give up already!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:50.81,0:40:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're torturing yourself. \NStop throwing your life away. {no clue what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:54.24,0:40:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything will become easy!
Dialogue: 10,0:40:55.75,0:40:58.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You will live in comfort \Nif you give your life up to me...
Dialogue: 10,0:41:14.98,0:41:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:21.00,0:41:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,D-Dragon, you... \NSo you still intend to defy me?
Dialogue: 10,0:41:26.65,0:41:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well, Dragon!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:27.75,0:41:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll put this syndicate's crest on the line for this bout! {/yakuza coat of arms}
Dialogue: 10,0:41:35.36,0:41:38.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With the crest on the line, \NDragon is not going to live,
Dialogue: 10,0:41:38.48,0:41:40.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,regardless of whether he wins or loses. {unsure}
Dialogue: 10,0:41:40.39,0:41:43.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Everyone present saw it that way.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:43.49,0:41:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:45.63,0:41:50.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The south 3rd round... Dragon started with a call of the 8-sou. {muzu check} {ok}
Dialogue: 10,0:41:50.53,0:41:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, I'll pon that. {missing page in manga, muzu} {or "That's a pon"}
Dialogue: 10,0:41:54.76,0:41:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon!
Dialogue: 10,0:41:57.76,0:41:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:05.55,0:42:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon! That hatsu is mine! Kan! {muzu} {ok TL, could be shorter: "I'll kan that Hatsu"}
Dialogue: 10,0:42:07.34,0:42:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Kai told me that
Dialogue: 10,0:42:09.16,0:42:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,getting into a calling war with you would cause nothing but trouble...
Dialogue: 10,0:42:11.98,0:42:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But I won't back down anymore!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:14.33,0:42:17.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to win the fights that you start. \NThat's...
Dialogue: 10,0:42:17.32,0:42:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way of the Yakuza!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:20.73,0:42:23.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not in this for much longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:23.06,0:42:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What was that?
Dialogue: 10,0:42:27.60,0:42:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:29.84,0:42:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon...!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:41.09,0:42:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon... Did you win? {muzu}{just remembered the shitpost TLs had it as "Are you winning son?"}{it was fine as it was, but could be shorter}
Dialogue: 10,0:42:53.49,0:42:56.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,If Dragon flips over that tile, he'll be killed for sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:56.67,0:42:59.97,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Everyone's attention was concentrated on Dragon's hands.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:04.50,0:43:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:19.86,0:43:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep yourself together, Kitajima. \NWhy are you taking out your gun?
Dialogue: 10,0:43:24.24,0:43:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,B-Boss...
Dialogue: 10,0:43:25.93,0:43:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down, Kitajima. \NDon't let your spirits down.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:29.44,0:43:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What would I do if you lost your cool? {believing manga}
Dialogue: 10,0:43:31.67,0:43:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In a battle, winning means heaven,
Dialogue: 10,0:43:33.94,0:43:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and losing means hell. \NIsn't that right, Dragon?
Dialogue: 10,0:43:39.85,0:43:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's start the final round, Dragon!
Dialogue: 10,0:43:43.38,0:43:44.64,Narrator,,0,0,0,,As the darkness disappeared,
Dialogue: 10,0:43:45.38,0:43:47.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the flow of time returned to the room.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:47.79,0:43:51.59,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Ever so slowly, with great reluctance,
Dialogue: 10,0:43:51.59,0:43:54.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the storm had turned to calm.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:58.66,0:43:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:00.39,0:44:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:07.90,0:44:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, I'm going to win!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:09.73,0:44:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:21.28,0:44:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon...
Dialogue: 10,0:44:22.79,0:44:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:30.33,0:44:32.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, I finally understand.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:32.77,0:44:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You are an incarnation!\NAn incarnation sent to me by god!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:37.06,0:44:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see that god truly detests me!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:39.97,0:44:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He sent you to this world... You, Dragon! \NWith the sole purpose of humiliating me!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:50.48,0:44:53.75,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Kai Group's Lieutenant Sotoda Yuji clearing his throat
Dialogue: 10,0:44:53.75,0:44:56.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was the signal to kill the Dragon.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:57.56,0:44:59.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,But then suddenly...
Dialogue: 10,0:45:01.79,0:45:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Kawachi!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:25.15,0:45:26.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:32.36,0:45:35.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop. Put down your guns.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:37.73,0:45:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Dragon, please hear me out before you go away for good.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:41.27,0:45:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This match is over.\NThere's nothing left to say.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:45.93,0:45:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it.
Dialogue: 10,0:45:46.89,0:45:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait I said!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:49.24,0:45:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Kitajima, what's the meaning of this?!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:51.17,0:45:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss, you can't kill Dragon! \NDon't do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:57.22,0:46:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That man is absolutely vital to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:00.05,0:46:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You must know this more than anyone else, boss.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:03.49,0:46:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason he was born into this world
Dialogue: 10,0:46:05.29,0:46:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,was to make you the greatest in the whole country!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:07.49,0:46:10.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because of his monstrous luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:10.45,0:46:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Boss, this is my last request...
Dialogue: 10,0:46:14.47,0:46:17.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't kill that man!
Comment: 0,0:47:00.80,0:47:00.83,Song,,0,0,0,,{ED}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.81,0:47:36.05,Song,,0,0,0,,It's too lonely up north {北はさびしすぎるから\N南行きの汽車に乗ります\Nわたしのことは 大丈夫\Nどこかに落ちついたら 手紙を出します}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.72,0:47:42.25,Song,,0,0,0,,I'll take the southbound train
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.86,0:47:48.83,Song,,0,0,0,,Don't worry about me
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.83,0:48:00.81,Song,,0,0,0,,I'll write to you when I'm settled somewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.81,0:48:06.75,Song,,0,0,0,,If you hesitate to leave me now, {いま 別れをためらえば\Nすがるしかない 女に なるわ\N愛した日々の重さに ああ耐えてます}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.75,0:48:12.85,Song,,0,0,0,,I'll be the one you'll have to cling to
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.85,0:48:27.57,Song,,0,0,0,,I've been holding on so tight to the weight of all the days I've loved you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.57,0:48:33.77,Song,,0,0,0,,I say good bye
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.77,0:48:46.09,Song,,0,0,0,,I'm a lonely woman looking for a town that suits me {孤独な女に 似合の街を探します}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.88,0:49:18.95,Song,,0,0,0,,Love is always cruel {愛はいつも残酷ね\N信じすぎた者を 傷める\Nあなたにもしも逢わなけりゃ\N平凡すぎるほどの 生活をしてたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.95,0:49:24.96,Song,,0,0,0,,It hurts those who believe in it too much
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.96,0:49:30.93,Song,,0,0,0,,If I hadn't met you
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.93,0:49:42.81,Song,,0,0,0,,I'd have had a life that was a little too ordinary
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.81,0:49:48.88,Song,,0,0,0,,Now, with no one to see me off, {いま 見送る人もなく\N動きはじめる 駅舎の灯り\Nながす涙の熱さに ああ耐えてます}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.88,0:49:54.89,Song,,0,0,0,,The lights of the station house begin to move
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.89,0:50:09.50,Song,,0,0,0,,I'm enduring the heat of my tears
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.50,0:50:15.87,Song,,0,0,0,,I say good bye
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.87,0:50:28.19,Song,,0,0,0,,Please understand, “good bye”\NIt's a word of love{わかって下さい ”さよなら”\N愛の言葉です}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.66,0:50:36.93,Song,,0,0,0,,If I hesitate to say goodbye now, {いま別れをためらえば\Nすがるしかない 女になるわ\N愛した日々の重さに ああ耐えてます\NI SAY GOOD BYE\Nわかって下さい ”さよなら”\N愛の言葉です}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.93,0:50:42.66,Song,,0,0,0,,I'll become a woman who has no choice but to cling to you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.66,0:50:57.58,Song,,0,0,0,,I've been so heavy with love, I've had to bear it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:57.58,0:51:03.89,Song,,0,0,0,,I say good bye
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.89,0:51:16.66,Song,,0,0,0,,Please understand that I say goodbye\NIt's the language of love
